# Dataverse Schema Design

- Every table/column/option set uses the publisher prefix
- Resolve the real publisher prefix from the project — never invent it or use `yourprefix`. Read it from `.env` (`PP_PUBLISHER_PREFIX=`), `pacaf.client.json` (`publisherPrefix`), the names already in `dataverse/planning-payload.json`, or the **Publisher Prefix** row in `README.md`; if all are missing, ask the user before creating schema.
- Dataverse schema, data, query, and solution operations are owned by the [Dataverse-skills](https://github.com/microsoft/Dataverse-skills) plugin — there are no `pacaf-validate` / `pacaf-generate` / `pacaf-register` scripts
- Discover existing schema first (`07a`), then provision with `dv-metadata`, then register with `pac code add-data-source`
- Option set values start at `{CHOICE_VALUE_PREFIX}0000`
- Schema mistakes are most expensive after data exists — plan first

Full details: `.github/instructions/07-dataverse-schema.instructions.md`
